{
  "texts": [
    "However, existing estimates for growth in algorithmic progress may not accurately represent the pace of progress with respect to more recent algorithms, even at the frontier.",
    "Difficulty of Early IdentificationScale-dependent innovations may appear modest at small scales, making it difficult to identify transformative improvements before committing substantial compute resources.",
    "The LSTM-to-Transformer transition showed only 6× gains at 10 15 FLOPs but more than 100× gains at 10 23 FLOPs.",
    "This suggests that limits to compute scaling pose obstacles not only to realizing efficiency gains but also to discovering them.",
    "This opens the possibility of algorithms that decrease performance at small scales, but which would improve performance if we scaled."
  ]
}